### Payment model populate chains

`Payment.js` schema defines:
```
bookingId ‚Üí ref: 'Booking'
customerId ‚Üí ref: 'User'
workerId   ‚Üí ref: 'Worker'
```
**No existing production code calls `Payment.populate()` currently.**  
The `MongoPaymentRepository.findRecentForWorker()` returns raw Payment documents (no populate). The clean Payment module will add `populate('bookingId')` support, verified in Phase 3.3's populate script.

### Review model populate chains

`Review.js` schema defines:
```
bookingId  ‚Üí ref: 'Booking'
customerId ‚Üí ref: 'User'
workerId   ‚Üí ref: 'Worker'
```
**No existing production code calls `Review.populate()` currently.**  
The aggregation pipeline in `review.js` uses `Review.aggregate()` (no populate). The clean module will add populate support.

### Chat model populate chains

`Chat.js` schema defines:
```
