## 7. Rollback Strategy

| Scenario | Rollback Action |
|---|---|
| Clean module files only created (Phase A/B/C) | Delete module folder ‚Äî zero legacy impact |
| After Chat proxy applied | `git checkout -- src/models/Chat.js` |
| After Review proxy applied | `git checkout -- src/models/Review.js` |
| After Payment proxy applied | `git checkout -- src/models/Payment.js` |
| Full Phase 3.4 rollback | `git revert <Phase3.4 commit>` ‚Äî single atomic revert restores all 3 models |
| Emergency production rollback | Replace proxy with original schema inline ‚Äî 3 files, ~10 lines each |

> [!CAUTION]
> Payment rollback requires immediate re-run of `tests/paymentRedirect.test.js` to verify wallet settlement integrity is preserved post-revert.

---

## 8. Verification Sequence Per Module

```
For each module (Chat ‚Üí Review ‚Üí Payment):

  Step 1: Run full test suite (pre-proxy baseline)    ‚Üí must be 23 passed
  Step 2: Build clean module (copy-first)
  Step 3: Run populate verification script
  Step 4: Apply proxy wrapper to models/[X].js
  Step 5: Run full test suite (post-proxy)            ‚Üí must be 23 passed
  Step 6: Run populate verification script again
  Step 7: Run live API smoke tests
```

**Additionally for Payment only:**
- Real wallet settlement verification (before/after wallet balance)
- Withdrawal transaction creation check

